msgid "Example"
msgstr ""

# e7403a28d09a4957bff96c03a74aab9c
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/hipes.en.rst:72
msgid ""
"ATS is run on port 80 and apache HTTP web server is run on port 8080 on "
"localhost (127.0.0.1)"
msgstr ""

# ae9e9ed54bf74067a51e24810ddb1bea
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/hipes.en.rst:74
msgid "The HIPES plugin is used in ``remap.config`` ::"
msgstr ""

# 935b91da6d1f46efa4e17c69ef7a4a4a
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/hipes.en.rst:80
msgid "The plugin remaps the incoming URL such as ::"
msgstr ""

# 3d0f403790804c4db57ea2bf745b4af2
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/hipes.en.rst:84
msgid "to the following ::"
msgstr ""

# 635b6839b64d45d587f8b21c6e318b11
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/hipes.en.rst:88
msgid ""
"The service ``svc_reverse.php`` fetches the ``url`` from the ATS again "
"and the plugin remaps the URL ::"
msgstr ""

# ef450c46337044729517d9c96fc21784
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/hipes.en.rst:92
msgid "to this URL ::"
msgstr ""

# 20a92f364d4948309156c1f87c6d11e6
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/hipes.en.rst:96
msgid ""
"5. In this example, the service ``svc_case.php`` fetches and transforms "
"the response of ``http://127.0.0.1/test.txt`` (which ATS proxies the "
"request to a local file) to upper case. And subsequently the service "
"``svc_reverse.php`` receives the response and reverse the order before "
"the response is sent back to the client by ATS."
msgstr ""

# 9b61ac8acc094c6da5320ea1901d8a65
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/hipes.en.rst:101
msgid "Notes on reducing traffic"
msgstr ""

# c58bec4c282846da9c21fce919bd6d32
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/hipes.en.rst:103
msgid ""
"There can be significant overhead using HIPES because the data can "
"traverse through ATS many times. Caching can be important to reduce "
"traffic to services/through ATS and can be achieved via a proper ``Cache-"
"Control`` header returned by the services. Another way to reduce traffic "
"through ATS is to have ATS to return 302 redirects to url for the "
"requests made by service, instead of proxying the requests to that url. "
"However, the service must then be able to follow the redirect. The down "
"side is that we cannot use ATS to cache intermediate results. Below is an"
" example of using redirect."
msgstr ""

# da974f4e0717400ca25a1f7e2893e022
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/hipes.en.rst:111
msgid "Modification to above example to reduce traffic using redirect"
msgstr ""

# fcef1431e1024abfaab2c18147f983b1
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/hipes.en.rst:113
msgid ""
"1. The service ``svc_reverse.php`` is modified to add a header of ``X"
"-HIPES-Redirect: 2`` to the request made against ``url``."
msgstr ""

# 9a1617c8f0824fe992333ff63aac142d
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/hipes.en.rst:116
msgid ""
"HIPES plugin will instruct ATS to return a redirect response to this url "
"::"
msgstr ""

# 8c521aa37c404bd3b28e40e2ef044cb3
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/hipes.en.rst:120
msgid "for the following request ::"
msgstr ""

# ed2025fc99f54f6ebd8242c40fb97861
#: ../../admin-guide/plugins/hipes.en.rst:124
msgid ""
"3.  The service ``svc_reverse.php`` is also modified to follow the "
"redirect. Thus the response of the service of ``svc_case.php`` will not "
"pass through ATS and will pass to ``svc_reverse.php`` service instead."
msgstr ""

